def: The quality of being intrinsical; intrinsicality.
An emerald-green variety of spodumene found in North Carolina;lithia emerald, -- used as a gem.
Of a fine blue color; azure.
Inflammation of the pia mater or of the arachnoid membrane.

A group of minerals having, a micaceous structure. They arehydrous silicates, derived generally from the alteration of some kindof mica. So called because the scales, when heated, open out intowormlike forms.
Quality or state of being unctuous. Sir T. Browne.
A prefix signifying chief, arch; as, architect, archiepiscopal.In Biol. and Anat. it usually means primitive, original, ancestral;as, archipterygium, the primitive fin or wing.
